70th Anniversary of Monthly Samil Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the People's Palace of Culture on November 30 to commemorate the 70th anniversary of the Monthly Samil, a revolutionary journal founded by President Kim Il Sung. 
 Present there were Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials of the press and printing organs, reporters, editors and media persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Chil Nam, editor-in-chief of Rodong Sinmun, said in his report that the foundation of the Monthly Samil, the organ of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland, was a revolutionary auspicious event which materialized the desire of the Korean revolutionaries and people to have a powerful ideological weapon to rouse the whole nation to the struggle for defeating the Japanese imperialists with concerted efforts and achieving national liberation and the birth of a model publication which held the most dignified and special position among revolutionary publications of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Monthly Samil with the form and content of its edition popularized and familiarized made a great contribution to implanting the seed of revolution in the hearts of the people, awakening the popular masses and rousing them to the sacred war for national liberation as a popular magazine which was read and loved by revolutionaries including soldiers of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army and members of the association as well as religionists and soldiers of the independence army, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The important exploit of the magazine is that it provided the tradition to be carried forward forever by the Juche-oriented press media. The history of leadership and exploits of Kim Il Sung who established the tradition of press media of our Party in the fierce flames of the anti-Japanese war were the proud course in which the might of the revolutionary idea of putting importance to writing-brush was demonstrated and the valuable wherewithal which brought the birth of a new era of Juche-oriented press media even under the complicated and difficult circumstances after the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership of the President many press media such as the newspaper of the Party, the Korean Central News Agency and the Radio and TV Broadcasting Committee of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea were founded in a short period after the liberation, so that the regular press system has been established and the Party and the people might step up the building of a new society with a powerful ideological weapon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our press media have experienced the heyday of its development under the leadership of Kim Jong Il who is successfully carrying forward the history of the press media pioneered by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of his leadership over the press media work of the Party is consistent with the days when he has defended the President's idea of the press and exploits with loyalty. And it is shining as the glorious revolutionary record which brought about a great surge in all fields of newspapers, news service, broadcasting and the press and roused the whole party and the army and all the people to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation under the banner of Songun.

Functions Held Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- A seminar, lecture, photo exhibition and film shows took place in Bangladesh, Ethiopia and Laos from Nov. 19 to 25 on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 On display in the venues of those functions were photos showing the immortal exploits performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean films "For the Liberation of the Country" and "Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the seminar held in Bangladesh said it is entirely thanks to Kim Jong Il's original Songun politics that the Korean people have frustrated the moves of the U.S. imperialists and their followers to firmly safeguard socialism and the sovereignty of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Ethiopian Youth Study Group of the Juche Idea in a lecture said that President Kim Il Sung's idea of attaching great importance to the army and the military affairs has been successfully put into practice by Kim Jong Il and the DPRK has become a military power as it is led by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The manager of the Laos-Korea Tin Company said at the photo exhibition and film show that Kim Jong Suk devotedly defended the headquarters of the revolution.

Declaration for Peace against War Released in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- Staffers of 47 Internet media in south Korea reportedly held a press conference in front of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Nov. 27 to release a declaration for peace against war.
 The declaration denounced the U.S. for interfering in the internal affairs of Korea as evidenced by pressurizing the south Korean "government" to halt the tour of Mt. Kumgang and the construction of the Kaesong Industrial Zone, while putting pressure upon the north through the adoption of a "resolution on sanction against the north" at the UN. It termed this an act of inciting the tension and confrontation on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration demanded the U.S. and the south Korean "government" take sincere measures to lift the sanctions against the north at once and achieve durable peace on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said that the staffers of the above-said Internet media would solidarize with other mediapersons and ordinary citizens and, furthermore, with the mediapersons and other compatriots of the north and the peace-loving forces of the world and wage a positive movement for peace against war.

Romania's National Day Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- Ioan Dedean, Romanian charge d'affaires ad interim in the DPRK, hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Nov. 30 on the occasion of the national day of Romania.
 Present there on invitation were Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Jo Jong Ho, vice-minister of Foreign Trade, Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys of different countries, staff members of foreign embassies and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were staff members of the Romanian embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Halt to Suppression of Participants in "November 22 All-People Action" Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly issued a statement titled "Immediately release the chairman of the Kwangju and South Jolla Provincial Federation of University Student Councils and stop suppression of the just struggle of people" on Nov. 27.
 The statement accused the south Korean "government" of rushing police forces to the scenes of "November 22 all-people action" to mercilessly crack down upon its participants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement demanded the "government" immediately halt the brutal suppression and, at the same time, release all those arrested. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called on all people to unite and check the conclusion of the "south Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement".

All Koreans Called upon to Achieve Great National Unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- Only when the seventy million Koreans go united can they decisively foil the moves of the U.S. imperialists for aggression war against reunification and witness the beginning of a new history of peace and reunification on this land.
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of Korean reunification is, in essence, a matter of rejoining the blood ties of the Korean nation artificially divided by outside forces and achieving the national unity and success in the reunification movement depends on how to attain the national unity, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of Korean reunification means the cause of the driving force of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This cause calls on the Koreans to be responsible for accomplishing it and carry it out by themselves according to their independent will and wishes. It is, therefore, a fundamental issue the solution of which requires primary efforts to bolster the driving force for reunification in the efforts to achieve the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If all Koreans in the north and the south and abroad pool their will and, on this basis, achieve the great national unity, they can settle the essential issue in accomplishing national reunification and then this will help solve the remaining matters with ease. It is in this context that the great national unity precisely means national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tremendous vitality of the great national unity has been proved by the successes made in the efforts to improve the inter-Korean relations and in the movement for reunification in recent years. To strengthen the great national unity presents itself as a more urgent issue in the present struggle to implement the June 15 joint declaration, taking it as a landmark of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the political parties and organizations and people of different social standings in the north and the south and abroad should support each other and take joint actions in the efforts to achieve the peace of the country and accomplish the cause of national reunification. The primary task facing them is to check and frustrate the U.S. imperialists' moves to ignite a new war and their attempt to perpetuate their presence in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National independence, reconciliation and the great unity of the Korean nation are what all Koreans unanimously desire and ardently wish. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans desirous of peace and independent reunification of the country should go united to achieve independence and great national unity. This is the only way for the Korean nation to survive and achieve reunification.

70th Anniversary of Monthly Samil Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Friday dedicates an editorial to the 70th anniversary of the foundation of the revolutionary publication Monthly Samil by President Kim Il Sung in the flames of the hard-fought anti-Japanese war.
 The editorial reads in part: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing through the requirements of the times and the developing revolution, the President accomplished the historic cause of founding   Monthly Samil, organ of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland, on Dec. 1, Juche 25 (1936) after founding the association, the first body of anti-Japanese national united front in Korea, in May that year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his care Monthly Samil displayed its might as an active agitator defending and implementing the Juche-oriented line and policy on the Korean revolution and an intimate educator and organizer powerfully rousing the broad masses to the anti-Japanese struggle and, in this course, provided the Juche-oriented idea and theory, precious experience and tradition, the eternal foundation stone for the building of the media of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The media of the WPK are media of the President either in view of their historical roots and the process of their building or of the proud course of their development adorned with victory and glory. The Korean people will remember through thousands of years the undying feats of the President in giving origin to the building of revolutionary media in the present era and establishing their great tradition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The precious tradition of the media of the WPK established by the President is now being successfully carried forward and developed on a higher stage by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il made public a lot of works including the work stressing the need to develop the media of the WPK into a powerful ideological weapon conducive to modeling the whole society on the Juche idea, thus providing valuable ideological and theoretical guidelines which should be upheld by those media down through centuries. This is the great exploits performed by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should carry forward pure and clean the tradition of the building of the revolutionary media established in the days of the anti-Japanese war, regarding it as precious wealth and all-powerful guideline.

Monthly Samil, Immortal Banner for National Liberation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- Seventy years have passed since President Kim Il Sung started publishing Monthly Samil, the organ of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland (ARF).
 Much upset by the brisk activities of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army (KPRA) and the ever-spreading ARF in the latter half of the 1930s, the Japanese imperialists were hell bent on repressing the revolutionary forces and severing the relations between the guerrillas and people while further intensifying the "punitive operations" against the KPRA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With a scientific penetration into the obtaining situation, the President initiated the founding of revolutionary publications, powerful propaganda and agitation means for rapidly propagandizing the revolutionary ideas and fighting slogans among the popular masses, uniting and training them organizationally and ideologically, and powerfully pushed ahead with the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the Nanhutou Meeting (February 27 to March 3, 1936), he built secret camps in the Mt. Paektu area to make a new upsurge of the Korean revolution and set up a publishing house there as part of the preparatory work for founding the organ of the ARF. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Basing himself on this preparation, he inaugurated Monthly Samil on December 1, Juche 25 (1936). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Monthly Samil was a mass politico-theoretical magazine with a basic mission to help realize the idea of the ARF to achieve the country's independence with the concerted efforts of the whole nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President found times to write articles to be carried in the magazine even in the fierce battles with the enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From the first days since its foundation, Monthly Samil played a tremendous role in rallying not only the members of the KPRA but also the broad sections of people in the patriotic struggle against the Japanese imperialists and arousing them in the struggle.

Spirit of Independence Asserted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- If any country gives up the anti-imperialist struggle, failing to see through the vulnerability of the imperialists and harboring an illusion about them, they can never be free from their domination, subjugation, exploitation and plunder.
 It is the way out for all countries and nations to carry out the revolution and construction by themselves and in their own way from their own viewpoint, combating any illusion about imperialism. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harboring any illusion about imperialism and counting on it is the most harmful matter which the world revolutionary people should guard against in the ongoing struggle to accomplish the human cause of independence, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists are leaving no means untried to create an illusion about capitalism, claiming that the hegemonic nature of the imperialists has changed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important for combating the illusion about imperialism is not to see just the appearance of the capitalist society but to see through its ulterior motive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The capitalist society is "heaven" for the bourgeois ruling class, but a hell on earth for the working class. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is not capitalism but socialism that guarantees dignity, rights and worthy life to an independent human being. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A policy for the people can be enforced only under the socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One should be vigilant against "aid" and "cooperation" much publicized by the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This kind of aid and cooperation are nothing but leverage for their exploitation, plunder, domination and subjugation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People should not be deceived by the imperialists' loudmouthed "peace." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is advocating its anti-terror war for aggression as a just war, painting itself as "an apostle of peace" and " a champion of democracy and human rights".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the peace-loving forces of the world are called upon to heighten their vigilance against the moves for aggression and war the imperialists are escalating under the deceptive signboard of "combating terrorism and ensuring peace" and intensify their struggle against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary political parties and people should firmly adhere to the independent stand against imperialism, strictly guard against any slightest manifestation of illusion about capitalism and combat it.

Campaign for Economizing Electric Power Stepped Up
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- A campaign for economizing and making an effective use of electricity is being vigorously launched in the DPRK as winter comes round.
 The campaign is participated in not only by power-producers but also by the institutions, industrial establishments, co-op farms and households across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The power plants are decreasing self-consumption of electric power and raising power factor of power system while the power transmission and dissemination units scrupulously organize the alternative production and effectively use the produced electric power by combining concentration, dispersion and supply of electricity with each other in an organic way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Factories and enterprises have developed transmission devices and save large quantities of electricity as compared with speed-fixed electric-motors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those in the construction field are drawing designs of buildings so as to economize electricity to the maximum by reflecting insulation, retaining of warmth and other conditions for electric economization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, illuminating lamps with high energy efficiency including compact lamps and small-sized power consumption measuring devices have been developed and introduced extensively.

Conservative Media's False Reports Blasted in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- A press conference was reportedly held in Seoul Monday to denounce conservative media for releasing false reports about "November 22 all-people action" under the co-sponsorship of the "National Press Trade Union," the Journalists Association of south Korea, the Cultural Solidarity and other media and cultural institutions and the Federation of Human Rights Organizations in south Korea.
  A press release read out at the press conference noted that the "all-people action" was an eruption of resentment against the present "government" and a just struggle to win the right to existence and settle by themselves the crisis facing the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It lashed out at the conservative media for backing the present "government" in its brutal suppression of the participants in the action and painting those who fought in defence of the right to existence as "mobs." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no justification for the conservative media to exist any longer as they are a group of criminals under the veil of mediapersons, the press release noted, demanding them apologize to the people for their crimes.

Scientific and Technological Presentation Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- A national scientific and technological presentation in the field of biology took place here on Nov. 29 and 30 on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of the publication of Kim Jong Il's famous work "On Further Developing Biology and Improving and Strengthening Work for Training Engineering Technicians."
 The presentation was divided into botanical, zoological, experimental biological, microbiological, biological engineering and biochemical panels. Presented there were at least 150 papers on the scientific and technological achievements helpful to rapidly developing biology to conserve and propagate the nation's biological resources, make an effective use of them, boost agriculture and stockbreeding and improve the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Achievements made in the researches into the physiological characteristics of the immortal flowers "Kimilsungia" and "Kimjongilia" and the technology of cultivating them drew keen interest of the participants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also introduced there were the successes registered in the cultivation of high-yielding crops and plants of economic value which have been put into practice and achievements made in the researches into breeding domestic animals of good stock and their scientific breeding method and in the development of feed and additives in the fields of stockbreeding and fish cultivation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Latest scientific and technological achievements and experience gained in the biological field through the application of IT, Nano technology and biological engineering technology were highly appreciated by the participants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also heard papers dealing with the successes made in the researches into the work to conserve and propagate the nation's biological resources and others helpful to the development of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prizes were awarded to the successful participants.

World AIDS Day Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 1 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson Friday dedicates an article to World AIDS Day.
 The day was instituted as a link in the whole chain of the global efforts and activities for preventing and controlling AIDS horribly threatening human lives while rapidly prevailing worldwide, notes the article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reviewing many successes recorded in its prevention and treatment with the efforts to prevent it gathering force worldwide, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il, the DPRK established the strategy of prevention and control of AIDS with orderly systems of its information, prognostication and watch, and examination across the country. On this basis, measures have been taken not to allow a single AIDS case. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 AIDS called "the plague of the 20th century" and "the leprosy of the 20th century" is still threatening the existence of humankind in the 21st century. However, there is no doubt that humankind will totally eradicate it on the earth and get rid of its threat.
